<div id='av_section_1' class='avia-section main_color avia-section-default avia-no-shadow avia-bg-style-scroll  avia-builder-el-1  el_after_av_slideshow_full  el_before_av_section  container_wrap fullsize'   ><div class='container' ><div class='template-page content  av-content-full alpha units'><div class='post-entry post-entry-type-page post-entry-2826'><div class='entry-content-wrapper clearfix'>
<div class="flex_column av_one_third  flex_column_div first  avia-builder-el-2  el_before_av_one_third  avia-builder-el-first  " ><div class='avia-image-container  av-styling-   avia-builder-el-3  el_before_av_textblock  avia-builder-el-first  avia-align-center '  itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageObject"  ><div class='avia-image-container-inner'><a href='http://nvma.ca/new-museum-2/new-museum/' class='avia_image'  ><img class='avia_image ' src='http://nvma.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/new-museum-polygon.jpg' alt='' title='new-museum-polygon'  itemprop="contentURL"  /></a></div></div>
<section class="av_textblock_section"  itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="https://schema.org/CreativeWork" ><div class='avia_textblock '   itemprop="text" ><h4>Proposal Keeps the Museum Dream Alive!</h4>
<h4></h4>
<p>NVMA has asked Polygon Homes to include a museum in their &#8216;Promenade at the Quay&#8217; project. Located at Carrie Cates Court/119-131 West Esplanade, the area is also known as &#8216;Site 8&#8217;. Learn more.  <a href="http://nvma.ca/new-museum-2/new-museum/">Details &amp; Public Information Session</a></p>
</div></section></div><div class="flex_column av_one_third  flex_column_div av-zero-column-padding   avia-builder-el-5  el_after_av_one_third  el_before_av_one_third  " style='border-radius:0px; '><div class='avia-image-container  av-styling-   avia-builder-el-6  el_before_av_textblock  avia-builder-el-first  avia-align-center '  itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageObject"  ><div class='avia-image-container-inner'><a href='http://nvma.ca/programs-and-events-2/' class='avia_image'  ><img class='avia_image ' src='http://nvma.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/6973-cropped-350x300-3.jpg' alt='' title='6973 cropped 350x300 (3)'  itemprop="contentURL"  /></a></div></div>
<section class="av_textblock_section"  itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="https://schema.org/CreativeWork" ><div class='avia_textblock '   itemprop="text" ><h4>Jane Walks &#8216;Shaketown&#8217;</h4>
<p>What&#8217;s happening outside the Fromme Building? Explore Lynn Valley’s history and heritage with a guided Jane’s Walk of the former Shaketown. Celebrate this historic neighbourhood with NVMA curator Karen Dearlove. <a href="http://nvma.ca/programs-and-events-2/"> Details.</a></p>
</div></section></div><div class="flex_column av_one_third  flex_column_div av-zero-column-padding   avia-builder-el-8  el_after_av_one_third  avia-builder-el-last  " style='border-radius:0px; '><div class='avia-image-container  av-styling-   avia-builder-el-9  el_before_av_textblock  avia-builder-el-first  avia-align-center '  itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageObject"  ><div class='avia-image-container-inner'><a href='http://nvma.ca/exhibits/' class='avia_image'  ><img class='avia_image ' src='http://nvma.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Cabin-front.jpg' alt='' title='Cabin-front'  itemprop="contentURL"  /></a></div></div>
<section class="av_textblock_section"  itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="https://schema.org/CreativeWork" ><div class='avia_textblock '   itemprop="text" ><h4>New Exhibit: The Water&#8217;s Edge</h4>
<p>Burrard Inlet&#8217;s north shore has been the site of First Nations activities, the home to many  artists as well as our industrial heritage. Learn more at our new exhibit,  &#8216;Water&#8217;s Edge&#8217;. Open Thursday to Sunday afternoons, noon to 5 pm. <a href="http://nvma.ca/exhibits/">More</a></p>
</div></section></div></div></div></div><!-- close content main div --></div></div><div id='portfolio' class='avia-section socket_color avia-section-large avia-no-shadow avia-full-stretch av-parallax-section avia-bg-style-parallax  avia-builder-el-11  el_after_av_section  el_before_av_section  av-minimum-height av-minimum-height-25 container_wrap fullsize'  data-section-bg-repeat='stretch' ><div class='av-parallax' data-avia-parallax-ratio='0.3' ><div class='av-parallax-inner socket_color  avia-full-stretch' style = 'background-repeat: no-repeat; background-image: url(http://nvma.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/banner-kei-1030x228.jpg); background-attachment: scroll; background-position: top left; ' ></div></div><div class='container' ><div class='template-page content  av-content-full alpha units'><div class='post-entry post-entry-type-page post-entry-2826'><div class='entry-content-wrapper clearfix'>
<div style='padding-bottom:10px;color:#000000;font-size:42px;' class='av-special-heading av-special-heading-h1 custom-color-heading blockquote modern-quote modern-centered  avia-builder-el-12  avia-builder-el-no-sibling  av-inherit-size'><h1 class='av-special-heading-tag'  itemprop="headline"  >Imagine&#8230;.A New Museum on the North Shore</h1><div class='special-heading-border'><div class='special-heading-inner-border' style='border-color:#000000'></div></div></div>
</p>
</div></div></div><!-- close content main div --></div></div><div id='about-us' class='avia-section alternate_color avia-section-large avia-shadow avia-bg-style-scroll  avia-builder-el-13  el_after_av_section  el_before_av_section  container_wrap fullsize' style = 'background-color: #f4f4f4; background-color: #f4f4f4; '  ><div class='container' ><div class='template-page content  av-content-full alpha units'><div class='post-entry post-entry-type-page post-entry-2826'><div class='entry-content-wrapper clearfix'>
<div style='padding-bottom:27px;font-size:50px;' class='av-special-heading av-special-heading-h1 meta-heading blockquote modern-quote modern-centered  avia-builder-el-14  el_before_av_hr  avia-builder-el-first   av-inherit-size'><div class ='av-subheading av-subheading_above ' style='font-size:18px;'><p>Don&#8217;t take our word for it&#8230;</p>
</div><h1 class='av-special-heading-tag'  itemprop="headline"  >What people say about a New Museum on the North Shore!</h1><div class='special-heading-border'><div class='special-heading-inner-border' ></div></div></div>
<div  class='hr hr-short hr-center  avia-builder-el-15  el_after_av_heading  el_before_av_testimonials '><span class='hr-inner ' ><span class='hr-inner-style'></span></span></div>
<div  data-autoplay='1'  data-interval='5'  data-animation='fade'  data-hoverpause='1'  class='avia-testimonial-wrapper avia-grid-testimonials avia-grid-2-testimonials avia_animate_when_almost_visible '>
<section class ='avia-testimonial-row'><div class='avia-testimonial av_one_half flex_column no_margin avia-testimonial-row-1 avia-first-testimonial'  itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" ><div class='avia-testimonial_inner'><div class='avia-testimonial-image'  itemprop="image" ><img width="80" height="80" src="http://nvma.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/test-jamieson.jpg" class="attachment-square size-square" alt="Eric Jamieson" srcset="http://nvma.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/test-jamieson-36x36.jpg 36w, http://nvma.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/test-jamieson.jpg 80w" sizes="(max-width: 80px) 100vw, 80px" /></div><div class='avia-testimonial-content '    itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="https://schema.org/CreativeWork" ><p class="p1">I have had a love affair with museums all my life; you can imagine my excitement at the prospect of a new museum.  Visible and vital, it will showcase our past and inform our future.</p>
</div><div class='avia-testimonial-meta'><div class='avia-testimonial-arrow-wrap'><div class='avia-arrow'></div></div><div class='avia-testimonial-meta-mini'><strong  class='avia-testimonial-name'    itemprop="name" >Eric Jamieson</strong><span  class='avia-testimonial-subtitle '    itemprop="jobTitle" >Author, "Tragedy at Second Narrows"</span></div></div></div></div>
<div class='avia-testimonial av_one_half flex_column no_margin avia-testimonial-row-1 avia-last-testimonial'  itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" ><div class='avia-testimonial_inner'><div class='avia-testimonial-image'  itemprop="image" ><img width="180" height="180" src="http://nvma.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/image001-180x180.jpg" class="attachment-square size-square" alt="Dan Miscisco" srcset="http://nvma.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/image001-80x80.jpg 80w, http://nvma.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/image001-36x36.jpg 36w, http://nvma.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/image001-180x180.jpg 180w, http://nvma.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/image001-120x120.jpg 120w" sizes="(max-width: 180px) 100vw, 180px" /></div><div class='avia-testimonial-content '    itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="https://schema.org/CreativeWork" ><p class="p1">Appealing to people of all ages, the new museum will showcase significant North Vancouver City and District events in an innovative, interactive and inspiring way. I am especially looking forward to presentations, exhibits, and stories that record the history of North Vancouver schools as well as team and individual sports accomplishments. What a fabulous project!</p>
</div><div class='avia-testimonial-meta'><div class='avia-testimonial-arrow-wrap'><div class='avia-arrow'></div></div><div class='avia-testimonial-meta-mini'><strong  class='avia-testimonial-name'    itemprop="name" >Dan Miscisco</strong><span  class='avia-testimonial-subtitle '    itemprop="jobTitle" >Educator, Coach, All-Star Sports Camp Director, Author</span></div></div></div></div></section>
<section class ='avia-testimonial-row'><div class='avia-testimonial av_one_half flex_column no_margin avia-testimonial-row-2 avia-first-testimonial'  itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" ><div class='avia-testimonial_inner'><div class='avia-testimonial-image'  itemprop="image" ><img width="80" height="80" src="http://nvma.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/test-sharon.jpg" class="attachment-square size-square" alt="Sharon Fortney" srcset="http://nvma.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/test-sharon-36x36.jpg 36w, http://nvma.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/test-sharon.jpg 80w" sizes="(max-width: 80px) 100vw, 80px" /></div><div class='avia-testimonial-content '    itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="https://schema.org/CreativeWork" ><p class="p1">The North Shore really needs family oriented, educational venues like this museum.  Accessible to everyone and showcasing our stories; it is exciting that we will soon have a facility that will truly bring North Shore history to life.</p>
</div><div class='avia-testimonial-meta'><div class='avia-testimonial-arrow-wrap'><div class='avia-arrow'></div></div><div class='avia-testimonial-meta-mini'><strong  class='avia-testimonial-name'    itemprop="name" >Sharon Fortney</strong><span  class='avia-testimonial-subtitle '    itemprop="jobTitle" >Grouse District Commissioner, Girl Guides of Canada</span></div></div></div></div>
<div class='avia-testimonial av_one_half flex_column no_margin avia-testimonial-row-2 avia-last-testimonial'  itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person" ><div class='avia-testimonial_inner'><div class='avia-testimonial-image'  itemprop="image" ><img width="80" height="80" src="http://nvma.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/test-francis.jpg" class="attachment-square size-square" alt="Daniel Francis" srcset="http://nvma.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/test-francis-36x36.jpg 36w, http://nvma.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/test-francis.jpg 80w" sizes="(max-width: 80px) 100vw, 80px" /></div><div class='avia-testimonial-content '    itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="https://schema.org/CreativeWork" ><p class="p1">Museums are places where communities discover themselves: their history, their diversity, their identity. I am very excited about the possibilities for discovery that a new museum will bring.</p>
</div><div class='avia-testimonial-meta'><div class='avia-testimonial-arrow-wrap'><div class='avia-arrow'></div></div><div class='avia-testimonial-meta-mini'><strong  class='avia-testimonial-name'    itemprop="name" >Daniel Francis</strong><span  class='avia-testimonial-subtitle '    itemprop="jobTitle" >North Vancouver writer/historian</span></div></div></div></div></section>
</div>

